  <diagram id="J6t5P9NqwGgxWxmexSOg" name="Basic Rendering">
    <mxGraphModel dx="2074" dy="1196" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-1" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 20px;&quot;&gt;Mesh Constructor Node&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;verticalAlign=top;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="50" width="290" height="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-2" value="Mesh Attribute" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#666666;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="114" y="116" width="142" height="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-3" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 20px;&quot;&gt;Mesh Render Node&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;verticalAlign=bottom;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="280" width="290" height="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-4" value="Mesh Attribute" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#666666;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="114" y="300" width="142" height="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-5" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;strokeWidth=3;" edge="1" parent="1" source="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-2" target="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-4">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-6" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Basic Rendering&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;Raylib covers the basic OpenGL essentials.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;However, we still need a way to collect the meshes AND splines for rendering. Below is the basic idea of rendering in AnimTrainer...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;1) We create a Mesh Constructor Node.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;The Mesh Constructor node input attributes are set dirty on creation. its compute will construct the node. This is a one time compute until we get fancier a bit later.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;2) The renderer will ask the graph to iterate over node types of: MeshRenderNode&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;3) call render...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="410" y="50" width="420" height="350" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-7" value="" style="endArrow=none;dashed=1;html=1;dashPattern=1 3;strokeWidth=2;rounded=0;" edge="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry width="50" height="50" relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="30" y="443" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="840" y="443" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-8" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Gizmo Rendering&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px; background-color: initial;&quot;&gt;1) I create the Time Node. This is a special node that is always created on graph creation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px; background-color: initial;&quot;&gt;2) A graph Update is called every frame&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px; background-color: initial;&quot;&gt;3) all the update does is set the Time node inputs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px; background-color: initial;&quot;&gt;The time node is really just a pass through node. Compute only pulls from input attrs and sets the output attrs. Thats all it does. Extremely simple. Any nodes downstream of a time node (aka need per frame update) will have compute called.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;WHY? This avoids having to create special node method update.We are just utilizing the internal dirty then compute.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;PROS:&lt;br&gt;I do not have to store the nodes that need updating separately. We are utilizing standard graph evaluation. No tricks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;IF a node needs an update every frame, they create an input attribute of type float and connect the output attribute of the time node to their input attribute. This also allows easily turning off updates by disconnecting from the time node.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;CONS:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;Every node that wants an update now has to explcitly register the float attribute and call a connect. This requires extra setup for this to work. The other potential con is that that we can potentially have many nodes connected to this node. Not sure if this is an issue, but its somethign to concider.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;I believe I can aleviate this con by calling a &lt;font color=&quot;#ff00ff&quot;&gt;Post Create method on the node factory&lt;/font&gt; and passing in the newly created node ID. This allows those types nodes that always need connecting to Time node to do the job there.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="30" y="470" width="610" height="680" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-14" value="" style="group;fillColor=#60a917;fontColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#2D7600;" vertex="1" connectable="0" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1380" y="620" width="290" height="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-9" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 20px;&quot;&gt;Axis Mesh Constructor Node&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;verticalAlign=top;" vertex="1" parent="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-14">
          <mxGeometry width="290" height="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-10" value="Mesh Attribute" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#60a917;fontColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#2D7600;" vertex="1" parent="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-14">
          <mxGeometry x="74" y="66" width="142" height="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-15" value="" style="group" vertex="1" connectable="0" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1100" y="850" width="330" height="150" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-11" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 20px;&quot;&gt;Gizmo Render Node&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;verticalAlign=bottom;" vertex="1" parent="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-15">
          <mxGeometry width="330" height="150" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-12" value="Mesh Attribute" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#60a917;fontColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#2D7600;" vertex="1" parent="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-15">
          <mxGeometry x="200" y="20" width="110.9" height="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-22" value="float attribute" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#d80073;fontColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#A50040;" vertex="1" parent="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-15">
          <mxGeometry x="30" y="20" width="98.28" height="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-13" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;strokeWidth=3;" edge="1" source="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-10" target="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-12" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
