        <mxCell id="kuPCAArl-eeqD7ysJQ-1-28" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Gizmo Rendering Issue....&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;Currently, in order for compute to get called, some code somewhere needs to call getData on the attribute handle. This is very inconvenient because some nodes (such as the render node) do not need an output attribute.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;It just needs compute to get called to render results.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;What do I do? I can make a a dummy `render` attribute.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;That seems kinda lame. The other option is I create a new method on the handle and nodes called:&lt;br&gt;computeIfNeeded()&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="960" y="1210" width="510" height="340" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
